		<hr size="1">Well my Bard is Rockin again. I stopped playing my Bard frequently when he hit level 56 because it was so difficult to get a Planes group with him. Every time I did get a group everyone liked having me there but people didn't know much about them.</P><P>One thing that LDoN has brought back to the game is the Bard. I didn't think Bards would be a welcome companion in LDoN because of the low DPS. I couldn't have been anymore incorrect. I get tells almost immediately from LDoN groups NEEDING a Bard. Hell, I even get tells when not LFG. That happened to me this morning when I was farting around in the Bazaar before I had to go to work.</P><P>In LDoN you need high DPS, Little downtime and single pulls. Well Bards HIGHLY contribute to the last two points mentioned above.</P><P>I will be playing my Bard some more now. My goal is to have a Level 65 Bard and 65 Shaman with 50 AA points each before EQ2 comes out. My Shaman is 65 with 30 AA now. My bard is almost 59.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
