		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 9/17/2003 12:57:44 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=62449">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Tolain Durant" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="mailto:danjnwo5@yahoo.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email Tolain Durant" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Tolain+Durant">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Tolain Durant" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2031357&TN=Bards+in+LDoN&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2031970&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">To repost what I posted in mainhall...</P><P><BR>Alot of this is speculation, so feel free to pick this post apart. There isnt much syntax here, just alot of random thoughts. sorry.</P><P>I ran several dungeons yesterday, and this is what my thoughts are. (compared to the beta, where failure was almost impossible)</P><P>My core group was in the level 60 range, with a monk, BL, and bard. Warriors, hybrids and casters came and went.</P><P>Heres my observation so far. This expansion has truely killed the "trinity". no clerics, enchanters, or warriors required, period.</P><P>Bards, paladins, and clerics using lull (bards lull being the best example, almost unresistable) make single pulling a snap, and CC was almost never needed.</P><P>Druids and shamans filled the healing gap, and hybrids and even a monk managed to tank in our 60ish dungeon.</P><P>Plat drops are decent, we averaged 1k per dungeon after all the junk was sold.</P><P>augs are decent, we saw about one per dungeon. I got afew nice +5 int augs.</P><P>bards are bar none the best pullers in this one, with the easily abused SSeye/lull trick. *nothing* in any dungeon was an issue. </P><P>Monks arent as good pullers due to time issues. you dont always have time to FD pull and split. However, bards arent very common 60+, on my server, so monks get their glory  People NEED to learn how to FD tag and split mobs. (monk pull + lull and a tag works great. gives clerics and other lull classes a bit more to do)</P><P>However, even when things got messy (aka- they got bored and made me stop doing crowd control) offtanking worked great, and most 'tank' classes could handle it.</P><P>That said, we were challenged. we finished most of our adventures within 5 minutes of deadline.</P><P>There is a secondary deadline, where you can earn about 1/5 of the points, if you finish the quest in under 30 minutes after the initial deadline.</P><P>Procs are revised. you now have a chance to proc every effect per swing. Now heres a thought about warriors and aggro.</P><P>warrior epic is going to have 3 aug slots, and includes an innitial hate proc, right? There are augs which proc hate. an example is the hate 2 aug. plug in the weapon, and you have a chance to proc a 200 hate effect. there are most likely much better effects, since hate 2 is only 400~ adventure points from what I hear.</P><P>Now, if a warrior uses all three aug slots for hate procs, he has a chance to proc multiple hate procs per swing. warrior epic is going to be one of very few pre- Ldon weapons with multiple aug slots.</P><P>Perhaps this will help warriors keep aggro? again, just random musings, I dont have proof or backup.</P><P>FT will be very common. a list here shows the first batch of LDoN gear. (most is targetted towards bards)</P><P><A HREF="http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=17946.topic" TARGET="_BLANK">http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=17946.topic</A></P><P>Note afew of the perks, including a new regen line that works like FT</P><P>Shiny Sandstone of Reconstruction type3aug Regeneration V(worn) CHEST (510) </P><P>Grainy Sandstone of Clarity type3aug Flowing Thought I(worn) (340) </P><P>Brilliant Enchanted Prism type3aug Flowing Thought II(worn) CHEST (510) </P><P>ternal Ice of Replenishment type3aug Regeneration II(worn) (340) </P><P>Weapon procs include everything from lifetaps to dds (return of ykesha!), and some augs have effects like ultravision.</P><P>Bards will be pleased to see that there are instrument augs, letting them not be as dependant on their epics.</P><P>Melees are very desireable now. this generation of players doesnt know how to dungeon crawl well, in general. </P><P>With the time limits, you dont have time to sit around medding. this makes mana-free DPS very popular. Rogues, monks, and rangers especially.</P><P>if I had to break it down into roles for the crawls</P><P>BL, ranger, monk, rogue, wizard, mage, necro -DPS<BR>pal, war, sk- tanks<BR>bards, enchanters- CC<BR>dru, shm, clr- healing</P><P>But its very interesting to note how much role overlap there is. if the shaman is main healing, beastlord usually deals with slow. clerics and paladins do limited CC/pulling, and ghetto mezzing (root) seems alot more popular.</P><P>This makes it so no one class is ever needed, another can always fill in.</P><P>Reward system is nice, but low levels dont get nearly enough adventure points. 65s would get 51, a 59 got 38ish. for most of the fails (we failed a good bit at first) you'de get 6-9 if you met the 30 minute after-dealine.</P><P>I probably have more to say, but forget most of it at this time. </P><P>/endreview.</P><P><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
