		<hr size="1">Yes! mez just plain rules for caster interupts. especially with all the Cheal mobs in later dungeons, and gaters.</P><P>Charisma is an essential to bards. The bare lowest it should ever be is 120. after 120 the effects arent as great, from what I hear.</P><P>For the longest time, everyone told me charisma was totally useless, then 2-3 months ago they proved it was the major factor in lull resists, missed notes,  memblur components, and other assorted goodies. I'm glad they finally proved it, I used to go on long crusades preaching its usefulness to deaf ears.</P><P>Ah! SS eye trick!</P><P><A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1513" TARGET="_BLANK">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1513</A></P><P>Singing steel helm is a truely amazing item. I bought it at level 40, and regretted it for 20-some levels, until I realized its awesome, awesome potential.</P><P>Our song lull songs don't require line of sight. that means we can stand behind a door, cast SSeye, move it into the room, and use the eye to target every monster in the area, while you lull each one from behind a wall. This is really useful in dungeons where they clump monsters in hard to see places so you get jumped.</P><P>Its amazing, the SS helm went from being my worst financial mistake, to one of the best items I own. I had even tried to sell mine for cheap for afew months. thankfully, no one bought it. its one of the most useful items a bard can own, giving him or her the ability to pull nearly anything single. It can also be used to scout dangerous areas. I can pretty much waltz anywhere in any dungeon I want using it.</P><P>The helms, unfortunatly, are rare. and I rarely ever see them for sale. when they are, 2-5k seems average.</P><P>While most will agree with me, I just dont see the appeal over STA. its like 4 hp per point at level 60, and when things are hitting for 300 damage a pop..It just doesnt seem like a worthy investment. thats just my playstyle though</P><P></P><P><BR>Message edited by: Tolain Durant (9/18/2003 12:44:19 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
