		<hr size="1">Tolian:</P><P>Getting back to you since I have several Hard wins under the belt.  I perfer the Hard level even though the point to time spent ratio isn't nearly as good, but the fun is considerably higher than the sleeper walks called normal.  And on the Hard levels, you are going to get 2-3 mobs every pull 80% of the time, so  you adjust or die.  If mez is unreliable (thought I have yet to see that problem in Miragel, GUK or Takizh Hard adventures), then root park or off tank.  Hard level mobs slowed are ranger tankable.</P><P><BR>Jokeber:</P><P>"THE KEY TO SINGLE PULLING IS start the next pull a little before the mob you are fighting is dead, and park mez one you just pulled if the origenal mob is not dead."</P><P>I am actually stunned you presented a decent rebuttal, and an accurate one no less.  If you have a puller that understands that concept, then I agree with you.  However, most of the time I see pullers who stand (or flop on the ground) there wasting time between kills making sure they bring singles while the rest of group is picking butt lint.</P><P><BR>"Why do that when I can single pull mobs and have a mob delivered and mezd before the one being killed is dead."</P><P>Well, if you are playing a bard, the primary reason why you should be pulling 2, at a time at the least, is because the time you spend away from the group is time they don't have the benefit of your songs.  Which, in the case of a bard twisting Marr, Warsong and Rizlona's, is a fairly drastic change compared to another class pulling where the group only loses that members DPS.  If you only have to leave every other mob instead of every mob, you increase your groups kill rate and increase the overall mana/regen.  If your group can handle 3 at a time, the total benefit to your group is higher again.  Of course, if you are the only manner of CC in the group and have to drop those other songs to mez, then its a wash, but I'm of the opinion that unless the mob is snare/root immune and you have no secondary tank, a bard is the worst option for CC.  Otherwise, let some else take care of it so the other 5 members of the group don't lose song effects, whether that means Off tanking or Root Parking.</P><P>Additionally, if your group has the melee capable of taking the damage and a healer that can cover both, its considerably faster to tank 2 mobs at once and let the mobs abuse themselves on DS on each tank, as well as DOT classes stack them up on both at the same time.  Mana regen is the key there, but with the levels of FT today, and things like KEI/VoG and Bard songs, thats probably not as much of an issue at the higher levels.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
